text: Washington County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,388. The county seat is Chatom. The county was named in honor of George Washington, the first President of the United States. == Geography == Washington County has a total area of 1,089 square miles. == References == Category:Alabama counties Category:1800 establishments in the United States Category:1800s establishments in Mississippi Territory
title: Washington County, Alabama
